<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="944" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d944">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control Italy/52:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-11T20:00:00-04:00">February 11, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>455. For Reinhardt. Your 259, January 25, 2 p.m. and 356 of February
                                3, 4 p.m. The President has approved the appointment of a French
                                representative to the Allied Control Commission on the same basis as
                                the Soviet representative. You should inform your French colleague
                                of this Government’s approval of French representation on the
                                Control Commission and take the earliest opportunity to concur with
                                the recommendation already endorsed by the other members of the
                                Advisory Council that a French representative be admitted to the
                                Commission.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>